      <title outputclass="H3_1_9" class="- topic/title ">
         <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">7.102</ph> Policy.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d401e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li otherprops="abc" outputclass="H5_abc" class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d408e17" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
                   Agencies shall perform acquisition
planning and conduct market research (see <xref href="FAR-i1114815.dita#i1114815"
                        base="i1114815"
                        outputclass="fm:Part"
                        class="- topic/xref ">part  10</xref>)
for all acquisitions in order to promote and provide for-</p>
               <ol id="d401e26" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li otherprops="123" outputclass="H6_123" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d408e30" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                         Acquisition of commercial items
or, to the extent that commercial items suitable to meet the agency’s
needs are not available, nondevelopmental items, to the maximum
extent practicable (<xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">10 U.S.C. 2377</xref> and <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C. 3307</xref>
                        <ph rev="FAC 2019-02 March 27, 2019" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [Why] Amend section 7.102 by removing from paragraph (a)(1) “41 U.S.C. 3307;” and adding “41 U.S.C. 3307);” in its place.?>); <?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] Technical Amendments?>and</ph>
                     </p>
                  </li>
                  <li otherprops="123" outputclass="H6_123" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d408e51" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                         Full and open competition (see <xref href="FAR-i1120119.dita#i1120119"
                              base="i1120119"
                              outputclass="fm:Part"
                              class="- topic/xref ">part  6</xref>)
or, when full and open competition is not required in accordance
with <xref href="FAR-i1120119.dita#i1120119"
                              base="i1120119"
                              outputclass="fm:Part"
                              class="- topic/xref ">part  6</xref>,
to obtain competition to the maximum extent practicable, with due
regard to the nature of the supplies or servicesto be acquired (<xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">10 U.S.C.2305(a)(1)(A)</xref> and <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C.
3306a)(1)</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li otherprops="123" outputclass="H6_123" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d408e72" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                        
                         Selection of appropriate contract
type in accordance with <xref href="FAR-i1105247.dita#i1105247"
                              base="i1105247"
                              outputclass="fm:Part"
                              class="- topic/xref ">part  16</xref>;
and</p>
                  </li>
                  <li otherprops="123" outputclass="H6_123" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d408e84" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(4)</ph>
                        
                         Appropriate consideration of
the use of pre-existing contracts, including interagency and intra-agency
contracts, to fulfill the requirement, before awarding new contracts.
(See <xref href="FAR-i8_002.dita#i8_002"
                              base="i1118176"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">8.002</xref> through <xref href="FAR-i1118226.dita#i1118226"
                              base="i1118226"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">8.004</xref> and <xref href="FAR-i1102787.dita#i1102787"
                              base="i1102787"
                              outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                              class="- topic/xref ">subpart  17.5</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li otherprops="abc" outputclass="H5_abc" class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d408e104" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  
                   This planning shall integrate
the efforts of all personnel responsible for significant aspects
of the acquisition. The purpose of this planning is to ensure that
the Government meets its needs in the most effective, economical,
and timely manner. Agencies that have a detailed acquisition planning
system in place that generally meets the requirements of <xref href="FAR-i1118917.dita#i1118917"
                        base="i1118917"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">7.104</xref> and <xref href="FAR-i1118935.dita#i1118935"
                        base="i1118935"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">7.105</xref> need
not revise their system to specifically meet all of these requirements.</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
